  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Smallholder Integrated Pig Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- To increase annual farm incomes of 1500 assisted resource-limited project participants by 60% through increased food production, value addition and access to profitable market by June 2015.
- To strengthen self-help, organizational capacities and gender relations of 55 assisted farmer groups  and 1500 project participants respectively through training on group leadership, group management and Gender equity issues by June 2015.
- To reduce the spread and negative impacts of HIV/AIDS among 75% of 1500 project participants by creating awareness through sensitization, training and facilitating access to Voluntary Testing and Counseling by June 2015.;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1800 households;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving small holders lives by increasing their income, improve their food security and nutrition through the introduction of piggery;</narrative>
